<exercise id="fs-id1678580" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1564900">
    <para id="import-auto-id2984853">A car engine moves a piston with a circular cross section of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>500</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">±</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>002</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>cm</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{7 "." "500" +- 0 "." "002"`"cm"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> diameter a distance of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>250</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">±</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>001</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>cm</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{3 "." "250" +- 0 "." "001"`"cm"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> to compress the gas in the cylinder. (a) By what amount is the gas decreased in volume in cubic centimeters? (b) Find the uncertainty in this volume.</para></problem>
